<DOC><DOCNO> AP890508-0116 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-08-89 1551EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Burma-Rebels     05-08 0167</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Burma-Rebels,0173</SECOND><HEAD>Troops Attack Rebels Near Thai Border</HEAD><DATELINE>MAE SOT, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Burmese troops attacked rebel basesnear the Thai border, and 40 people were killed and 70 wounded,Thai military sources said Monday.   Thai authorities evacuated 100 villagers after 2,500 soldiersattacked Karen strongholds at Wan Kha and Ban Wang Takian on Sunday.   Several artillery shells were reported to have fallen insideThai territory and Burmese troops crossed into Thailand during theassault, the military source said on condition of anonymity.   About 30 Burmese soldiers and 10 guerrillas were killed, he said.   Also Sunday, 3,000 Burmese civilians fled into Thailand at SaiLuad to escape fighting at a third border location, Myawaddy.   Karen rebels are among a dozen ethnic minority groups fightingfor greater autonomy from the Rangoon government. The government inrecent months has intensified its campaign against the Karens andhas severely disrupted the cross border trade that sustains theirinsurgency.   The Karen strongholds are located along Thailand's westernborder with Burma.</TEXT></DOC>